HaXR is a client and server library for XML-RPC in Haskell.


REQUIREMENTS

* A Haskell implementation such as GHC (http://www.haskell.org/ghc/)
or Hugs (http://www.haskell.org/hugs/) with support for Cabal.

* HaXML (http://www.cs.york.ac.uk/fp/HaXml/)

* The Haskell Cryptographic Library (http://www.haskell.org/crypto/)

* The HTTP package (http://www.haskell.org/http/)

INSTALLATION

* Configure:

$ ./Setup.lhs configure

* Compile:

$ ./Setup.lhs build

* Install (as root):

# ./Setup.lhs install

DOCUMENTATION

You can build Haddock documentation from the source code:

$ make haddock
